The domain of every polynomial function f is R.
There are three possibilities for the range.
(a) If the degree is odd, then ran (f) = R.
(b) If the degree is even and positive, then
(i) ran (f) = [k, ∞) if an > 0;
(ii) ran (f) = (-∞, k] if an < 0,
where k is the y-coordinate of the lowest point for case (i), or the highest point for case (ii), of the
graph.
